{"lemma":"عَضُدِ","slug":"عَضُدِ","root":"ع.ض.د","root_slug":"ع-ض-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ض-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَضُد","root":"عضد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n29435","n29436","n29437","n29438","n29439","n29440","n29441"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"upper arm, bracchium, humerus","examples":[{"text":"فِي ذِرَاعِ ٱلْإِنْسَانِ ثَلَاثَةُ عِظَامٍ: اِثْنَتَانِ فِي ٱلسَّاعِدِ ٱسْمَاهُمَا ٱلزَّنْدُ وَٱلْكُعْبُرَةُ وَوَاحِدَةٌ فِي ٱلْعَضُدِ.","english":"There are three bones in the human arm: two in the lower arm (called the ulna and the radius) and one in the upper arm."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something or someone that gives man strength, assistant etc.","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, lateral, brink, border, region, quarter, area, tract, boundary","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"لوجع الْأَسْنَان وضع ورق الكبيكج على عضد العليل من جَانب سنه العليل سكن الوجع من سَاعَة وَإِن أحدث فِي العصب قرحَة فَيَنْبَغِي أَن يعالج بعد ذَلِك.","english":"For tooth-ache put leaves of spearwort onto the ill spot from the side of the aching tooth and it will attain relief from the ache within an hour and if a sore spawn in the tissue then it should be treated after that."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be strong for, to succor, to support, to aid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reinforce, to corroborate, to strengthen, to be strong for, to sustain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَضَدَ (ʕaḍada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is lopped from trees, cuttings"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29435","headword_ar":"عَضْدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence: ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDaAdN","text_ar":"عَضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29436","headword_ar":"عُضْدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29437","headword_ar":"عِضْدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29438","headword_ar":"عَضَدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAd","text_ar":"اَعْضَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arms"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of which they are slit"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in those parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.)       -A2-  And (tropical:)  What is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees; (S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiydN","text_ar":"عَضِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoDuwdN","text_ar":"مَعْضُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaDadu","text_ar":"العَضَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lopped, from trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves that are made to fall by beating trees, and used as food for camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiydN","text_ar":"عَضِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves scattered off from a tree for camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence: ―         -b2-  and again, near the middle, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n29439","headword_ar":"عَضُدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) which is the most common form of the word, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDidN","text_ar":"عَضِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) of the dial. of Asad, (O, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuDudN","text_ar":"عُضُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, O, Msb, K,) of the dial. of Tihámeh, (AZ, TA,) or of El-Hijáz, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDadN","text_ar":"عَضَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDodN","text_ar":"عَضْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) of the dials. of Temeem and Bekr, (O, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuDodN","text_ar":"عُضْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDodN","text_ar":"عِضْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the last three of which are said to be contractions of the first or second, or variants thereof formed to assimilate them to other words preceding them; (TA;) all masc. and fem.; (L;) or fem. only; (Lh, TA;) or masc. in the dial. of Tihámeh; (AZ, L;) or fem. in the dial. of Tihámeh, and masc. in the dial. of Temeem; (AZ, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEidN","text_ar":"سَاعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) i. e. [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper half of the arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the elbow to the shoulder-blade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the elbow and the shoulderblade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, O, Msb, K,) of a human being: (L:) [and in a beast, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaDahu","text_ar":"اَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;) in this case like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDudN","text_ar":"اَعْضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or only the latter, (L,) which is used in a poem of Sá'ideh Ibn-Ju-eiyeh as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of bees. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaA^a mino $aHomK EaDudiY","text_ar":"مَلَاَ مِنْ شَحْمٍ عَضُدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the story of Umm-Zara, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled with fat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not peculiarly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":", but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my whole body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for when the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"becomes fat, the whole body becomes so. (O, L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaDodu","text_ar":"العَضْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaDudu","text_ar":"العَضُدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA;) and so [app. any of its variants mentioned above, and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaADidN","text_ar":"عَاضِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAdapN","text_ar":"عِضَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) And it is also used for [its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the Kur xviii. 49, in which the sing. form is said to be employed for the sake of agreement with the other verses [preceding and following], that they may all end with singulars: (TA:) but one also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo","text_ar":"هُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudiY","text_ar":"عَضُدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdiY","text_ar":"اَعْضَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are my aiders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K, TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudiY","text_ar":"عَضُدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is my support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stay."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fat~a fiY EaDudihi","text_ar":"فَتَّ فِى عَضُدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke some of the intentions, purposes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"designs, of his aiders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people of his house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and separated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, them from him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought to injure him by diminishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impairing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in number"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of his house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T and O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft","text_ar":"فت"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fat~a fiY A^aEoDaAdihi","text_ar":"فَتَّ فِى اَعْضَادِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in the present art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fat~a fiY EaDudiY wahad~a rukoniY","text_ar":"فَتَّ فِى عَضُدِى وَهَدَّ رُكْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke my strength, and dispersed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separated, my aiders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft","text_ar":"فت"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the part so called, of a man, is a mean of strength to him. (L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sana$ud~u EaDudaka biA^axiyka","text_ar":"سَنَشُدُّ عَضُدَكَ بِاَخِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxviii. 35], means, accord. to Zj, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will aid thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assist thee, by thy brother."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the armpit; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDadN","text_ar":"عَضَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road; (O, L; [in this sense written in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDodN","text_ar":"عَضْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAdapN","text_ar":"عِضَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from which the wind blows. (L.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an outward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent, part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion; a quarter region,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K;) of a house, and of anything: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudu Alr~akaAy^ibi","text_ar":"عَضُدُ الرَّكَايِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, surrounding the camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other beasts, used for riding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimoliko A^aEoDaAda AlA_ibili","text_ar":"اِمْلِكْ اَعْضَادَ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Have thou possession of the tracts adjacent to the camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direct thou aright the course of the camels, so that they may not wander away to the right and left."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDadN","text_ar":"عَضَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) which last is a pl. of the two preceding words, as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuDuwdN","text_ar":"عُضُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A raised enclosing border,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such borders, of built work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, K,) &c., (S, L,) of a watering-trough or tank, and of a road, &c., (K,) or of anything, (S, O,) such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAd","text_ar":"اَعْضَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a watering-trough or tank, which are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broad and thin stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up around the brink;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from the place whence the water flows into it, to its hinder part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a watering-trough or tank: (IAar, L:) or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAd","text_ar":"اَعْضَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"are its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAd","text_ar":"اَعْضَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a portion of sown land that is separated from the parts adjacent to it by ridges of earth, for irrigation, are its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised borders that confine the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoDaAdu AlmazaAriEi","text_ar":"اَعْضَادُ المَزَارِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundaries between the portions of sown land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDod","text_ar":"عَضْد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) is also syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiydN","text_ar":"عَضِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiydapN","text_ar":"عَضِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A row"},{"kind":"text","text":"of palm-trees: (O, K:) the first of these words is mentioned by Hr as occurring in a trad., and is thus expl.: but others say that it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiydN","text_ar":"عَضِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which, accord. to As, signifies a palm-tree"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having such a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trunk that one can reach from it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDodaAnN","text_ar":"عِضْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) he adds that when it exceeds the reach of the hand it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jab~aArapN","text_ar":"جَبَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaA Aln~aEoli","text_ar":"عَضُدَا النَّعْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAdataAhaA","text_ar":"عِضَادَتَاهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaA $iraAki","text_ar":"عَضُدَا شِرَاكِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aEoli","text_ar":"النَّعْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two branches of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAk","text_ar":"شِرَاك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sandal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"described voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u*unN","text_ar":"اُذُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two appertenances, of the sandal, that lie upon the foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaA Alr~aHoli","text_ar":"عَضُدَا الرَّحْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two pieces of wood that are attached to the fore part of the camel's saddle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the lower portions of its fore part"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiT","text_ar":"وَاسِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (Lth, O, L:) or, accord. to AZ,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper portions of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalifataAni","text_ar":"ظَلِفَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a mistake for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinowaAni","text_ar":"حِنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel's saddle, next"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pieces of wood called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAqiY","text_ar":"عَرَاقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below them being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalifataAni","text_ar":"ظَلِفَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are the lower parts of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinowaAni","text_ar":"حِنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiT","text_ar":"وَاسِط"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^ax~arap","text_ar":"مُوَخَّرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, L. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalifapN","text_ar":"ظَلِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". In a similar manner, also, the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaAni","text_ar":"عَضُدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in relation to a horse's saddle: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarabuwsN","text_ar":"قَرَبُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b8-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDaAdN","text_ar":"عَضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2073}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","AZ","Th","L","IAar","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n29440","headword_ar":"عَضِدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a complaint of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.) ―         -b2-  A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDadN","text_ar":"عَضَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has drawn near,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approached, to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaAni","text_ar":"عَضُدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (O, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the watering-trough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b4-  A male [wild] ass"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has drawn together the she-asses"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^utuna","text_ar":"الاُتُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from their several quarters"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino jawaAnibihaA","text_ar":"مِنْ جَوَانِبِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"); as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaADidN","text_ar":"عَاضِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) the former occurs in a verse of El-Akhtal, describing a sportsman shooting at [wild] asses. (O.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN EaDidapN","text_ar":"يَدٌ عَضِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arm of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion between the elbow and the shoulder-blade"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is short."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN EaDidapN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ عَضِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A short upper arm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDaAdN","text_ar":"عَضَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["O","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n29441","headword_ar":"عُضُدٌ","root":"EDd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudN","text_ar":"عَضُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}